{"timestamp":"2026-03-12T08:06:50.909Z","level":"WARN","message":"codex stderr","iteration":24,"chunk":"codex\nUpdated the backlog prompt context so task-ledger drift no longer looks like clean backlog exhaustion. In [promptBuilder.ts](/home/admin/Documents/repos/Ralph/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/src/prompt/promptBuilder.ts#L620), `buildTaskContext` now inspects task-graph preflight errors and, for `replenish-backlog` or `selectedTask === null`, emits explicit drift language instead of the misleading “actionable backlog is exhausted” line when the ledger is inconsistent. The prompt wiring already passes preflight context through [promptBuilder.ts](/home/admin/Documents/repos/Ralph/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/src/prompt/promptBuilder.ts#L1043), and the new task-context branch uses that same signal.\n\nAdded regression coverage in [promptBuilder.test.ts](/home/admin/Documents/repos/Ralph/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/test/promptBuilder.test.ts#L495) for the concrete failure mode: a replenish-backlog prompt with `completed_parent_with_incomplete_descendants` now warns about task-ledger drift and explicitly avoids claiming clean exhaustion.\n\nValidation ran and passed:\n`cd ralph-codex-vscode-starter && npm test -- --test-name-pattern=\"replenish-backlog|tracker drift|task-ledger drift\"`\n`cd ralph-codex-vscode-starter && npm run validate`\n\nAssumptions or blockers: no new blockers. I assumed the intended fix was operator-visible prompt context, since preflight and status reporting already surfaced the drift and the misleading wording remained in backlog/task context.\n\nKnown limitations or follow-up work: this change only adjusts prompt/task-context wording; it does not change prompt-kind selection or automatic task-file remediation behavior.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"selectedTaskId\": \"T23.2\",\n  \"requestedStatus\": \"done\",\n  \"progressNote\": \"Surfaced task-ledger drift in replenish-backlog and no-selected-task prompt context so inconsistent task graphs no longer present as clean backlog exhaustion; added regression coverage and passed validate.\",\n  \"validationRan\": \"cd ralph-codex-vscode-starter && npm test -- --test-name-pattern=\\\"replenish-backlog|tracker drift|task-ledger drift\\\" && npm run validate\"\n}\n```\n"}
