{"timestamp":"2026-03-12T08:16:00.420Z","level":"WARN","message":"codex stderr","iteration":25,"chunk":"codex\nChanged files: [src/prompt/promptBuilder.ts](/home/admin/Documents/repos/Ralph/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/src/prompt/promptBuilder.ts), [src/ralph/iterationEngine.ts](/home/admin/Documents/repos/Ralph/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/src/ralph/iterationEngine.ts), [src/ralph/preflight.ts](/home/admin/Documents/repos/Ralph/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/src/ralph/preflight.ts), [src/ralph/statusReport.ts](/home/admin/Documents/repos/Ralph/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/src/ralph/statusReport.ts), [test/preflight.test.ts](/home/admin/Documents/repos/Ralph/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/test/preflight.test.ts), [test/promptBuilder.test.ts](/home/admin/Documents/repos/Ralph/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/test/promptBuilder.test.ts), [test/statusReport.test.ts](/home/admin/Documents/repos/Ralph/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/test/statusReport.test.ts). Validation regenerated the corresponding `out/` artifacts.\n\nThe fix is narrow: when Ralph has no selected task because the durable task ledger is inconsistent, preflight summaries now say selection is blocked by task-ledger drift, status adds an explicit top-level drift summary, and `replenish-backlog` prompt selection/strategy stop describing the situation as clean backlog exhaustion. Prompt-kind selection now carries task-graph diagnostics forward so the operator-visible reason matches the real blocker.\n\nValidation results: `cd ralph-codex-vscode-starter && npm run validate` passed. I also ran focused compiled regressions for preflight, status report, and prompt builder drift wording.\n\nAssumptions or blockers: none. I did not modify `.ralph/tasks.json` or `.ralph/progress.md`. The only unrelated dirty file remains [../.ralph/logs/extension.log](/home/admin/Documents/repos/Ralph/.ralph/logs/extension.log).\n\nKnown limitations or follow-up work: this change surfaces ledger drift more clearly in summaries and prompt selection, but it